    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, the veto power is definitely a big issue. but wouldn't a historian also argue that the UN provides a necessary framework for dialogue that prevents things from being even worse? like, even if it can't stop every war, it provides humanitarian aid and a place for countries to talk so they don't just resort to immediate violence? it seems like a huge part of their success is just keeping the channels open.",
